Economy:
Income :

The income represent the passive gold you will receive every round

You get 250 gold after each combat

Interest :

You will get an extra 10 gold after each combat for every 100gold you have (max . 100gold)

Ex: you have 500 gold => you will get 250 + 50 = 350

Your goal is to get to 1000 Gold to maximise you interest

Victory :

A victory will grantyou 50 Gold.

You will get an extra 20 gold for each win streak (consecutive wins) you have (max 100gold)

EX: you have 1000 gold and won 4 round in a row => you will get 250 (base) + 100 (interest) + 50 (vicory) + 4*20 (4 wins streak) = 480g

Defeat :

A defeat will grant you 15 gold for each lost point of life

A opposite to win streak you can lose streak and you will get 15 gold for each lose streak (max 60)

Ex : you have 1000 gold and lost 3 rounds in a row and last combat you lost 8 hp => you will get 250 (base) + 100 (interest) + 120 (8 (hp lost)*15) + 45 (3 (lose streak)*15) = 515 gold

Cards :
Each card will add 1/2/3 level to the branch depending on the rarity of the card. (Ex :normal regen card will put 1 point in regen branch, legendary fury card will put 3 point in fury branch).

Card can have 2 branches.

There are 3 type of cards:

Normal cards:

Cost 100gold

add 1 point to the branch

Can be dropped from any branch level

There are 72 card for each branch with ~93.5% drop rate

Epic card

Cost 200gold

Add 2 points to the branch

Can be dropped if the branch is already level 10+

There are 3 card for each branch with ~3.9% drop rate

Legendary cards

Cost 300gold

Add 4 points to the branch

Can be dropped if the branch is already level 20+

There are 2 cards for each branch with ~2.6% drop rate

Branches :
As said before, buying cad will give you points in the card branch.

Branches have passive ability (Ex: Ultimate branch passive are ultimate damage and mana regen)

Thoses passive have 4 levels

each level will boost the passive

Branches level up treshold are 4/10/20/40

Tips :
You want to stay above 1000gold to max your interest

The faster you reach level 20 on a branch, more chance to get a legendary card for that branch.

Play on the counter card

You have many "branch" immunity card (Ex : poison immunity) that will decrease damage from this branch

Some branches are natural counter (Ex : fury counter frost and vise-versa)

Check the remaining pool for each branch often, if many people are buying the same branch oyu need to adapt (play counter branch, level up fast to get legendary, etc...)